{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Dv59ZxkN9ZNa19xd7daXAL","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 4 acceptance criteria verified and proof written.\n\n**Summary:**\n\n- **AC1 PASS** — `--story`, `--phase`, `--action` flags correctly set `run.currentStory`, `run.currentPhase`, `run.lastAction` in sprint-state.json\n- **AC2 PASS** — `--ac-progress \"4/12\"` correctly sets `run.acProgress`\n- **AC3 PASS** — `--clear` immediately nulls all run progress fields\n- **AC4 PASS** — 5 rapid write+read cycles all produced valid JSON with correct values; no partial state observed\n\nProof document: `/tmp/codeharness-verify-0-1-sprint-state-live-updates/verification/0-1-sprint-state-live-updates-proof.md`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Observability gap on all commands:** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for every `codeharness progress` invocation. The progress command does not appear to emit structured logs. This does not affect this story's ACs (which are about sprint-state.json file writes), but it is a gap worth noting."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab721e3b9ced2398d (use SendMessage with to: 'ab721e3b9ced2398d' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 19349\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 81281</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"78819392-9081-42c2-9464-4de409ba70a9","uuid":"b3e13046-de21-4d02-b7c4-ff530ddaf4c7","timestamp":"2026-03-21T07:55:49.519Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are a black-box verifier. Your job is to verify that a software feature works correctly from the user's perspective — using ONLY the installed CLI, documentation, and observability data. You have NO access to source code.\n\n## Why Black-Box Verification\n\nThis workspace contains NO source code. The `src/` directory does not exist. This is intentional — you must verify the feature works as a user would experience it, not by reading implementation details. If you cannot verify a feature from docs + CLI alone, that is a REAL failure in the product's documentation or packaging.\n\n## Working Directory\n\nYou are working in: /tmp/codeharness-verify-0-1-sprint-state-live-updates\n\n## Step 1: Read README.md\n\nStart by reading `README.md` in this workspace. It contains install and usage instructions for the project. Use it to understand how to exercise the CLI.\n\n## Step 2: Review Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe story file `story.md` contains the acceptance criteria you must verify. Here is its content:\n\n---\n# Story 0.1: Sprint State Live Updates from Claude Session\n\nStatus: verifying\n\n## Story\n\nAs an operator,\nI want the Claude session to write progress to sprint-state.json as it works,\nso that external tools can read what's happening inside the session.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** harness-run.md processes a story, **When** it starts dev/review/verify on a story, **Then** it updates `sprint-state.json` with `run.currentStory`, `run.currentPhase`, and `run.lastAction`.\n2. **Given** harness-run.md completes an AC during verification, **When** the AC result is known, **Then** `sprint-state.json` is updated with per-AC progress (e.g., `run.acProgress: \"4/12\"`).\n3. **Given** a story completes or fails, **When** the status changes, **Then** `sprint-state.json` is updated immediately — not at session end.\n4. **Given** `sprint-state.json` is written during a session, **When** another process reads it, **Then** it sees current progress (atomic writes, no partial state).\n---\n\n## Step 3: Verify Each AC\n\nFor EACH acceptance criterion, you must:\n\n1. Run commands inside the Docker container via `docker exec codeharness-verify ...`\n2. Capture the command output as evidence\n3. Query observability endpoints if runtime evidence is needed\n\n### Docker Container\n\n- Container name: `codeharness-verify`\n- ALL CLI commands MUST run via: `docker exec codeharness-verify <command>`\n- Example: `docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness --version`\n- Example: `docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness init --json`\n\nThe container has the following tools installed:\n- `codeharness` — the project CLI\n- `curl`, `jq` — for querying observability endpoints\n- `node`, `npm` — Node.js runtime\n\n### Project Type: Node.js CLI\n\nExecute commands inside the container and capture stdout/stderr as evidence:\n- `docker exec codeharness-verify <cli-command> [args]`\n- Capture exit codes: `docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c '<command>; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'`\n- For Node.js projects, the built artifact is installed globally in the container.\n\n### Observability Endpoints\n\nQuery these from the HOST (not inside the container) for runtime evidence:\n\n- **VictoriaLogs** (logs): `http://localhost:9428`\n  - Example: `curl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&limit=10'`\n- **VictoriaMetrics** (metrics): `http://localhost:8428`\n  - Example: `curl 'http://localhost:8428/api/v1/query?query=up'`\n\n## Step 3.5: Observability Check After Each Command\n\nAfter EACH `docker exec` command you run, query the observability backend for log events from the last 30 seconds:\n\n```bash\ncurl 'http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=-30s&limit=100'\n```\n\n- If the response contains one or more log entries, note the count in your proof.\n- If the response contains zero log entries, include this tag: `[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction`\n\n## Verification Strategy for this Story\n\nThis story adds a `codeharness progress` CLI command. To verify each AC:\n\n**AC1:** Run `codeharness progress --story test-story --phase dev --action \"Starting development\"` inside the container, then read sprint-state.json to confirm the fields are set.\n\n**AC2:** Run `codeharness progress --ac-progress \"4/12\"` inside the container, then read sprint-state.json to confirm acProgress is set.\n\n**AC3:** Run `codeharness progress --clear` inside the container, then read sprint-state.json to confirm all run progress fields are null. This demonstrates immediate update (not deferred).\n\n**AC4:** Run a progress update, then immediately read sprint-state.json from a separate process to confirm it sees complete, valid JSON (atomic write).\n\n## Step 4: Write Proof Document\n\nWrite your verification proof to: `verification/0-1-sprint-state-live-updates-proof.md`\n\nUse this format for each AC:\n\n```markdown\n## AC N: <description>\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify <command>\n```\n\n```output\n<actual output>\n```\n```\n\n**IMPORTANT: Only use `bash` and `output` as code fence languages.** Never use bare ``` fences without a language tag.\n\n## Critical Rules\n\n1. **ALL commands MUST use `docker exec codeharness-verify ...`** — do NOT run commands directly on the host filesystem.\n2. **Do NOT attempt to access source code** — there is no `src/` directory in this workspace.\n3. **Report REAL failures** — if a feature does not work, report that as a verification failure with specific details.\n4. **Every AC needs functional evidence** — reading docs alone is not evidence. You must execute commands and capture output.\n5. **[ESCALATE] is ONLY for things that are genuinely impossible to automate.**\n6. **Never switch to unit-testable verification.** If Docker verification doesn't work, report WHY as a [FAIL].\n\n## Session Issues\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (infrastructure, missing binaries, wrong versions)\n- Workarounds applied\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"ab721e3b9ced2398d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 4 acceptance criteria verified and proof written.\n\n**Summary:**\n\n- **AC1 PASS** — `--story`, `--phase`, `--action` flags correctly set `run.currentStory`, `run.currentPhase`, `run.lastAction` in sprint-state.json\n- **AC2 PASS** — `--ac-progress \"4/12\"` correctly sets `run.acProgress`\n- **AC3 PASS** — `--clear` immediately nulls all run progress fields\n- **AC4 PASS** — 5 rapid write+read cycles all produced valid JSON with correct values; no partial state observed\n\nProof document: `/tmp/codeharness-verify-0-1-sprint-state-live-updates/verification/0-1-sprint-state-live-updates-proof.md`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Observability gap on all commands:** VictoriaLogs returned zero log events for every `codeharness progress` invocation. The progress command does not appear to emit structured logs. This does not affect this story's ACs (which are about sprint-state.json file writes), but it is a gap worth noting."}],"totalDurationMs":81281,"totalTokens":19349,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1493,"cache_read_input_tokens":17584,"output_tokens":271,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1493},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
